The paper deals with the problem of low-tubal-rank tensor recovery, which is a topic in signal processing and machine learning. The use of tensor singular value decomposition (t-SVD) and regularized tensor nuclear norm minimization (RTNNM) model suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of Information Theory (cs.IT) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the restricted isometry property (RIP) and its variants, which are important concepts in compressed sensing and numerical analysis, indicating that the paper may also fit into the sub-categories of Numerical Analysis (cs.NA), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
